{"questionId":"9074332","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An uncharged parallel plate capacitor C is connected to a cell of emf 12 V, a resistor R&nbsp;and another resistor of resistance 20 MΩ.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/855b7f89a047667afae64107441a009b8e249dbf.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The switch is then connected to Y and C discharges through the 20 MΩ&nbsp;resistor. The voltage <em>V</em><sub>c</sub> drops to 50 % of its initial value in 5.0 s. Determine the&nbsp;capacitance of C.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup></math> «F»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for a bald correct answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074332","referenceCode":"21N.2.HL.TZ0.c.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The switch is then connected to Y and C discharges through the 20 MΩ resistor. The voltage Vc drops to 50 % of its initial value in 5.0 s. Determine the capacitance of C.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.3 – Capacitance","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}